---
import BlogPostLayout from '../../../layouts/BlogPostLayout.astro';
---
<BlogPostLayout
  title="How to play as Kinsano - Halo Wars 2"
  description="Master Morgan Kinsano in Halo Wars 2 with this guide covering her fire-based abilities, Flame Warthog strategies, and powerful combo attacks for demolishing enemy bases."
  category="Guides"
  publishedDate="Published on January 31, 2026"
  dateIso="2026-01-31"
  ogImage="/img/HW-Guides/Kinsano-2.jpg"
  youtubeId="tpVJOFNYM20"
  tags={['Halo Wars 2']}
>
  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
    Morgan Kinsano is one of the most fun leaders in Halo Wars 2, though she's been nerfed significantly over the years. She was the first DLC leader released for Halo Wars 2.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 text-cyan-300">Pros</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Anti-Infantry Focus</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Powers are great against infantry</li>
    <li>Inferno is excellent for taking out bases, especially UNSC bases without shields</li>
    <li>Flame Wall is wonderful for destroying enemy infantry and bases</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Kinsano Cyclops Hero Unit</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>One of the fastest heroes in the game with High Torque Joint upgrade</li>
    <li>Comparable speed to Shipmaster and Arbiter</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Unit Drops</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Hell Drop (veteran Hellbringer squad)</li>
    <li>Flame Warthog Drop</li>
    <li>Second most unit drops among UNSC leaders after Captain Cutter</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Strong Fire Theme</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Many offensive powers centered around fire</li>
    <li>Great for pressuring opponents</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Cons</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Weak Against Air</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Flame Warthogs are not effective against air</li>
    <li>None of her powers are good against air</li>
    <li>Kinsano Cyclops cannot attack air</li>
    <li>Must rely on Combat Tech Marines or Wolverines for anti-air</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Vulnerable to Vehicles</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Infantry focus leaves vulnerability to Wraiths and Scorpions</li>
    <li>Gets outplayed often due to anti-infantry based design</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Limited Late Game Identity</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>No specialty beyond flame units</li>
    <li>Released before developers established strong leader themes (unlike Yap Yap or Serina)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Build Order</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Starting Out</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Build supply pads and tell Marines to gather crates</li>
    <li>First leader point: <strong class="text-cyan-400">Heat of Battle</strong> (upon making a kill, units briefly gain damage bonus and increased armor)</li>
    <li>Identical to Decimus's Killing Frenzy</li>
    <li>Hellcharge was nerfed and isn't as viable anymore</li>
    <li>Upgrade supply pads and build a generator</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Two Paths Forward</h3>

  <ol class="list-decimal list-inside mb-6 ml-4 space-y-2">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Rush Strategy</strong>: Build two barracks and continuously pump Hellbringers</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Standard Build</strong>: Build second generator for faster tech 2</li>
  </ol>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Second Tech</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Build two garages for double pumping Flame Warthogs</li>
    <li>Get a mini base with an armory</li>
    <li>Train Kinsano and get the Flame Wall upgrade</li>
    <li>Build an expo</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Flame Warthog Strategy</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Overwhelming early tech 2 with Flame Warthogs works well</li>
    <li>Tech 1 is usually heavy infantry, giving Flame Warthogs a type advantage</li>
    <li>Fun fact: The Flame Warthog passenger has a rocket launcher (single projectile for air)</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Leader Points Progression</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Third Point</strong>: Napalm Missiles (not Redline - save that for later when upgraded)</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Fourth Point</strong>: Flame Hog Drop (3 veteran Flame Warthogs, costs 850 supplies, no power)</li>
    <li><strong class="text-cyan-400">Fifth Point</strong>: Inferno (recommended before Firestorm Battle Group)</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Tech 3 Considerations</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Incendiary Grenades</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Contentious upgrade in the community</li>
    <li>Replaces constant attack with grenade launcher style</li>
    <li>Probably worth getting, but results may vary</li>
  </ul>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Army Composition</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Don't spam Flame Warthogs as the match progresses</li>
    <li>Transition to standard units based on opponent's strategy</li>
    <li>Get vehicle upgrades</li>
    <li>Build Nightingales for support</li>
    <li>Eventually build a barracks and upgrade Hellbringers for better Hell Drops</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Combo Attack Strategy</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">The Fire Drop Combo</h3>

  <ol class="list-decimal list-inside mb-6 ml-4 space-y-2">
    <li>Drop Flame Wall to take down shields</li>
    <li>Drop Inferno on the base</li>
    <li>Use Hell Drop for veteran Hellbringers with Dispersion Nozzles</li>
    <li>Fire Napalm Missiles across everything</li>
    <li>Drop Flame Warthogs if available</li>
    <li>Use Firestorm Battle Group (grants Hellcharge to all units in the landing zone)</li>
  </ol>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Firestorm Battle Group Tip</h3>

  <p class="mb-4">
    Even if you didn't get the Hellcharge upgrade, Firestorm Battle Group grants Hellcharge to all units in the LZ. Great way to get Hellcharge effect without spending the leader point.
  </p>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Defensive Uses</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Choke Points</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Inferno works great at natural choke points</li>
    <li>On Sentry, the ramps are perfect for Inferno placement</li>
    <li>Take advantage of grouped enemy units</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Kinsano Cyclops Tips</h2>

  <h3 class="text-xl font-bold mb-3 mt-6 text-cyan-200">Speed Advantage</h3>

  <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4 ml-4">
    <li>Moves faster than the rest of your army</li>
    <li>When selecting all units, they move at the same speed</li>
    <li>Click Kinsano individually to have her move ahead</li>
    <li>Useful for escaping tough situations or getting somewhere first</li>
  </ul>

  <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold mb-4 mt-8 text-cyan-300">Summary</h2>

  <p class="text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
    Kinsano excels at fire-based offense and anti-infantry combat. Her weakness is air and vehicles. Early game Flame Warthog pressure is effective, but you must adapt your army composition as the match progresses. Use her powerful ability combos to demolish enemy bases, but be mindful of counters.
  </p>
</BlogPostLayout>
